## A


### Agile

Agile is a project management methodology which focuses on delivering value and outcomes to users quicker than traditional [waterfall](#waterfall) approaches.

Instead of delivering everything in one go, features are delivered iterativley by teams working on focused tasks to deliver an outcome. 

<a href="https://agilemanifesto.org/" target="_blank">Read the Agile Manifesto (opens in new tab)</a>

<a href="https://www.gov.uk/service-manual/agile-delivery" target="_blank">Agile delivery on GOV.UK Service Manual (opens in new tab)</a>

### Alpha

A phase in the delivery lifecycle which is after [Discovery](#discovery) and before [Beta](#beta).

In the alpha phase, you're expected to test your riskiest assumptions, build prototypes, try different solutions to solve your problems to meet you user needs.

You may also have a [service assessment](#service-assessment) before the end of your alpha phase.

